title: Recess At Last
author: Gerald Aungst

---

scene: opening

Mrs. McClintock stops right in the middle of explaining how to add fractions with unlike denominators. She looks around at twenty-four kids all sneaking peeks out the window at the recess yard, and she smiles. After what the weather lady on Channel 8 called the worst, wettest winter ever, she has to know it's a lost cause.

"OK, we'll finish this tomorrow. Clear your desks and line up for recess."

Yes! You've been waiting for this since you woke up. A sunny day and a brand new pair of sneakers, the white ones you're supposed to keep clean for your cousin's party Saturday. You wore them anyway. Nothing is going to ruin your recess today.

Then Mrs. McClintock catches your eye. "Hold on there, Jamie. You too, Sam. You two never turned in your Explorer packets. You have to finish them before you can go out."

Choices:
- Sit back down at your desk and glance at Sam -> classroom

---

scene: classroom

Two rows over, Sam is digging through his desk like the packet might be hiding under all his junk. It isn't. Sam almost never does his homework, but he always looks for it really hard.

Mrs. McClintock sits at her desk, waiting. You need four things before you can go outside: a pencil, your finished packet, your backpack with your hat and mittens, and your coat. The pencil is the easy one. It's right there in your desk. The packet is the one that's really gone.

Choices:
- Get a pencil from your supply box, then deal with the closet -> supplybox
- Go straight to Mr. Bradley's room, since the packet is the real problem -> packet_first
- Ask Mrs. McClintock if she has a spare pencil -> ask_mcclintock

---

scene: supplybox

The supply box is right there in your desk. Your mom got you the huge dorky one instead of the small cool one, but it still works. Pencil in hand in about ten seconds.

Now the closet.

Choices:
- Head into the coat closet -> closet

---

scene: ask_mcclintock

She looks up from her papers.

"Don't you have one of your own, Jamie?"

You start to explain. She holds up a hand and opens her desk drawer. Then she stops and sets a single pencil on the corner of her desk.

"You can borrow this one," she says. "But you'll have to leave me something to hold onto until you bring it back." She looks down at your feet. "One of those nice new sneakers ought to do it."

A shoe. For a pencil. And not just any shoe, the brand new ones you're saving for Saturday. There is no way that is happening today.

"Never mind," you say. "I'll get my own."

She almost smiles. "Your coat is probably in the lost-and-found, by the way. Mrs. Walker keeps everything down there."

Choices:
- Go back to your desk and dig out your supply box -> supplybox_after_asking

---

scene: supplybox_after_asking

Your supply box is still in your desk, right where it always is. Pencil in hand in about ten seconds.

Now the closet.

Choices:
- Head into the coat closet -> closet

---

scene: packet_first

The pencil is right there in the supply box. Ten seconds, done. The coat and the backpack can wait. The packet is the real blocker, and it's all the way over in Mr. Bradley's room.

Choices:
- Head out into the hallway -> hallway_nobackpack

---

scene: closet

Oh, this is a total disaster. Mrs. McClintock always tells everyone to hang up their coats and bags in the morning, but of course they just dump them in a heap on the floor. Everyone's stuff is tangled together. You can see the corner of your yellow backpack near the bottom. Somebody left a pair of muddy boots right in the middle of everything.

Choices:
- Work carefully around the boots -> closet_careful
- Just dig in. You'll be careful enough -> closet_fast

---

scene: closet_careful

You take your time. The backpack comes loose with the hat and the mittens still inside. Your sneakers stay perfectly white. You'll have to stop at the lost-and-found for your coat, though. You're pretty sure that's where it ended up.

Choices:
- Head out into the hallway -> hallway_clean

---

scene: closet_fast

The backpack comes out fast. So does a streak of mud across your left sneaker, off the edge of one of those boots. Small. Brown. There's no pretending you didn't see it.

You'll still have to stop at the lost-and-found for your coat.

Choices:
- Head out into the hallway -> hallway_scuffed

---

scene: badend_caught

You make it about twenty feet before Mrs. Parker steps out of the side entrance with a coffee cup and a look of total surprise.

The talk after that is short and very uncomfortable. You sit outside her office for what feels like three years. She isn't even mad, which is somehow worse. She just seems puzzled that you would do this when you were so close to being done.

By the time you get back to Room 9 the whistle has blown. Mrs. McClintock looks at you, looks at the empty spot where your packet should be, and tells you to sit down and finish it after recess. She doesn't say it in a mean way. That almost makes it worse.

You're at your desk, the sneakers still on your feet, while everyone else is outside.

THE END

---

scene: badend_whistle

She takes the packet just as the whistle blows outside. She looks at you with something that isn't quite sympathy and isn't quite an apology.

"You can go out tomorrow, Jamie. The weather's supposed to be nice all week."

You look down at your sneakers. Saturday is still coming. The party will be fine. It doesn't help as much as it should.

THE END

---

scene: ending_brief_kickball_clean

You make it into the game for two turns before the whistle blows. You didn't slide. The sneakers are fine. You're out of breath and grinning.

It wasn't the recess you pictured this morning. But you were out there, and the sneakers are perfect for Saturday.

THE END

---

scene: ending_brief_sunshine_clean

You find a spot in the sun just as the whistle blows. Four minutes of warmth. The sneakers are spotless.

It was enough. Barely, but enough. Saturday is going to be great.

THE END

---

scene: door_rushing_clean

The playground door. Sunshine. Kickball. Mud. The whistle could blow any minute. You have to pick fast.

Choices:
- Go for the kickball game -> ending_brief_kickball_clean
- Stay on the blacktop -> ending_brief_sunshine_clean

---

scene: mcclintock_rushing_clean

She takes the packet. Her eyes move down it fast. She nods.

"Go ahead, Jamie. Hurry up."

You're already moving.

Choices:
- Get to the door -> door_rushing_clean

---

scene: library_latecheck_toolate

Miss Feeney checks your answer in about thirty seconds and tells you you had it right all along. Then comes the walk back to Room 10, and the longer walk back toward Room 9, and somewhere in there you already know what the clock is going to say.

Choices:
- Head back with the packet -> badend_whistle

---

scene: folder_clean_coat_unc_b_direct

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> mcclintock_rushing_clean
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_toolate

---

scene: folder_toolate

The yellow folder. Your Explorer packet is right inside, finished, in your own handwriting. You did do this. You should feel good about it.

Mostly you feel the clock. You grab the packet and head for the door.

Choices:
- Hurry back toward Room 9 -> badend_whistle

---

scene: room10_browse_toolate

You know you shouldn't. You look anyway. A whistling frog on a seven-cent stamp from Bermuda, an index card your brother wrote about somebody named Brancusi. The stamps are wonderful and the minutes are gone, and that clock in the back of your head is pounding now.

Choices:
- Grab the folder and run -> folder_toolate

---

scene: room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_b

You're in the stamp room. Posters of stamps, framed envelopes, fat binders, a big map of the world with a stamp by every country. Any other day you could look around in here forever.

Your brother's desk is easy to find, with his name tag taped on top. Out the window the playground is full and loud and you are not in it. You can tell this is taking longer than it should.

Choices:
- Grab the yellow folder and go -> folder_clean_coat_unc_b_direct
- Look around at the stamps for a minute. They'll be quick -> room10_browse_toolate

---

scene: ending_muddy_clean

The mud got the sneaker. The kick was worth it. You knew that when you decided, and you'd decide the same way again.

Saturday is going to be complicated. Right now it doesn't feel complicated at all.

THE END

---

scene: kickball_ontime_clean

Your friends see you coming and somebody waves you over. The mud is real and you know it. So is the game. First time up, your kick sails over the outfield. Second time up you go for first base without quite deciding to, and the mud sprays, and your left sneaker takes the whole thing.

Choices:
- Slide into first base anyway -> ending_muddy_clean

---

scene: ending_careful_clean

The sneakers are perfect. Saturday is going to be great. You got twelve minutes of recess, and right now twelve minutes feels like everything.

The sun is warm on your face and the blacktop smells like spring.

THE END

---

scene: blacktop_ontime_clean

Your friends wave you toward the field. You point at your sneakers and shake your head. Somebody laughs. Somebody shrugs. You find a spot in the sun and tip your face up into it.

Choices:
- Soak up the sun -> ending_careful_clean

---

scene: ending_doorway_clean

You step out, and somewhere between the door and the blacktop it hits you: kickball isn't the whole thing. The sun is warm, your friends are right there, and your sneakers are perfect. Twelve minutes of this is plenty.

Maybe tonight you'll sneak the sneakers back into the box. Nobody ever has to know.

THE END

---

scene: doorway_ontime_clean

You don't move right away. You just let it happen: the warmth through the glass, the voices, the smell of spring. Then somebody from your class spots you through the fence and yells your name.

Choices:
- Push the door open and step out into the sun -> ending_doorway_clean

---

scene: door_ontime_clean

The playground door. Through the glass: sunshine, blacktop, your class playing kickball on the field beyond. The field is still muddy from last week's rain. Nobody has spotted you yet. You have time.

Choices:
- Run for the kickball game, even if the field ruins the sneakers -> kickball_ontime_clean
- Stay on the blacktop and find your friends -> blacktop_ontime_clean
- Just stand here a second -> doorway_ontime_clean

---

scene: mcclintock_ontime_clean

She takes the packet and reads it over for a moment. Then she looks up.

"You may go outside, Jamie."

Eight words. The best eight words of the whole school year.

Choices:
- Get to the door -> door_ontime_clean

---

scene: library_latecheck_clean_coat_a

Miss Feeney is still at the desk. She checks your answer in about thirty seconds and tells you you had it right all along. Then comes the walk back to Room 10, and then the walk back toward Room 9, and both of them feel a lot longer than they did the first time.

Choices:
- Head back with the packet -> mcclintock_rushing_clean

---

scene: folder_clean_coat_unc_a_direct

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> mcclintock_ontime_clean
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_clean_coat_a

---

scene: folder_clean_coat_unc_b_browsed

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers. You've already burned a few minutes on the stamps, too.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> mcclintock_rushing_clean
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_toolate

---

scene: room10_browse_clean_coat_unc_a

You can't help it. Your brother has an index card about a sculptor named Constantin Brancusi pinned next to a stamp from Romania. There's a first-day cover with a whistling frog on it, a seven-cent stamp from Bermuda. You lose three whole minutes and you find every one of them worth it.

Choices:
- Okay, grab the folder -> folder_clean_coat_unc_b_browsed

---

scene: room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_a

You're in the stamp room. It's the same size as your own classroom, but it doesn't feel anything like it. Mr. Bradley collects stamps and they're everywhere: posters of stamps, framed envelopes from the first day each stamp came out, fat binders full of them. One whole bulletin board is a map of the world with a different stamp pinned by every country.

Your brother's desk is easy to find. His name tag is taped right on top, with a number line and a plastic cup of Spongebob pencils.

Choices:
- Get the yellow folder out of his desk -> folder_clean_coat_unc_a_direct
- Look around at the stamps for a minute -> room10_browse_clean_coat_unc_a

---

scene: hallend_clean_coat_unc_friendly

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. Mrs. Walker had your coat on the back hook before you finished asking, black with yellow and orange patches, still warm. It's over your arm now.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_b
- Go borrow Mr. Frank's master key -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_a

---

scene: lostandfound_late_busy

You still have to grab your coat, and the office is busy now. Two parents at the counter, a teacher making copies, Mrs. Walker on the phone. You stand there for what feels like a very long time before she's free. The coat takes thirty seconds once she gets to you. It was the waiting that cost you.

Choices:
- Hurry back to Room 9 -> badend_whistle

---

scene: folder_clean_nocoat_unc_b_direct

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> lostandfound_late_busy
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_toolate

---

