---

scene: hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_friendly

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. You still have to swing back for your coat.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_b
- Go borrow Mr. Frank's master key -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_a

---

scene: frank_clean_unc

He's cheerful and in no hurry at all. You tell him you're trying to get to Mr. Bradley's room. He mentions the lost-and-found before you even ask, and then he taps the giant ring of keys on his belt and says he's got a master key for every room in the building if you ever need it. ("Ubiquitous" was the challenge word last week and you still sort of remember what it means. Mr. Frank's keys are ubiquitous.)

The whole thing takes a couple of minutes you didn't really have.

Choices:
- Duck into the office for your coat from the lost-and-found -> hallend_clean_coat_unc_friendly
- Head for Mr. Bradley's room -> hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_friendly

---

scene: hallend_clean_coat_unc_unengaged

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. Mrs. Walker had your coat on the back hook before you finished asking, black with yellow and orange patches, still warm. It's over your arm now.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_a

---

scene: hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_unengaged

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. You still have to swing back for your coat.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_a

---

scene: junction_clean_unc_unengaged

Mr. Frank is mopping a little way down the hall. Through the office window you can see Mrs. Walker doing about four things at once. The lost-and-found rack is just inside the office door.

Mr. Frank gives you a friendly nod and goes back to his mopping.

Choices:
- Stop and talk to Mr. Frank -> frank_clean_unc
- Duck into the office for your coat from the lost-and-found -> hallend_clean_coat_unc_unengaged
- Keep walking toward Mr. Bradley's room -> hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_unengaged

---

scene: junction_clean_unc_friendly

Mr. Frank is mopping a little way down the hall. Through the office window you can see Mrs. Walker doing about four things at once. The lost-and-found rack is just inside the office door.

"Get that pencil sorted out?" Mr. Frank calls, leaning on his mop. You nod. "Good. Go on, then." It's a small thing, but it helps.

Choices:
- Duck into the office for your coat from the lost-and-found -> hallend_clean_coat_unc_friendly
- Keep walking toward Mr. Bradley's room -> hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_friendly

---

scene: hallend_clean_coat_unc_wary

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. Mrs. Walker had your coat on the back hook before you finished asking, black with yellow and orange patches, still warm. It's over your arm now. Down at the far end you spot Mr. Frank and his master key. You could ask him. You decide not to.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_clean_coat_unc_b

---

scene: hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_wary

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. You still have to swing back for your coat. Down at the far end you spot Mr. Frank and his master key. You could ask him. You decide not to.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_clean_nocoat_unc_b

---

scene: junction_clean_unc_wary

Mr. Frank is mopping a little way down the hall. Through the office window you can see Mrs. Walker doing about four things at once. The lost-and-found rack is just inside the office door.

You see Mr. Frank glance up from his mop. You keep your eyes straight ahead and keep moving. You'd rather not get into it.

Choices:
- Duck into the office for your coat from the lost-and-found -> hallend_clean_coat_unc_wary
- Keep walking toward Mr. Bradley's room -> hallend_clean_nocoat_unc_wary

---

scene: sidedoor_clean

The door opens easy. The air outside is warm and smells like spring and wet blacktop. Around the corner you can hear voices. Your class. Playing kickball. Right now. Without you. Your sneakers are still perfect, and the blacktop is right there.

One step. Two steps.

"Hey."

Mr. Frank is ten feet away with a mop. He's not mad. He just looks patient, and very sure of himself.

Choices:
- Say sorry and go back inside -> junction_clean_unc_friendly
- Slip back inside without a word -> junction_clean_unc_wary
- Keep going -> badend_caught

---

scene: room10_inside_toolate

You're in the stamp room. Stamps on the walls, stamps in binders, a whole map of the world made of stamps. There's no time to enjoy any of it.

Your brother's desk is right there, name tag on top. Out the window your class looks impossibly far away, and the clock over the door is not on your side.

Choices:
- Grab the yellow folder and go -> folder_toolate
- Look at the stamps for just a second, even now -> room10_browse_toolate

---

scene: folder_clean_coat_vis_b_direct

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You find the one answer you'd worried about and remember exactly what Miss Feeney told you. She was right. You were right.

You did finish this. Somehow it ended up in your brother's folder.

Choices:
- Grab the packet and go -> mcclintock_rushing_clean

---

