Mr. Frank is mopping a little way down the hall. Through the office window you can see Mrs. Walker doing about four things at once. The lost-and-found rack is just inside the office door.

Mr. Frank gives you a friendly nod and goes back to his mopping.

Choices:
- Stop and talk to Mr. Frank -> frank_clean_vis
- Duck into the office for your coat from the lost-and-found -> hallend_clean_coat_vis_unengaged
- Keep walking toward Mr. Bradley's room -> hallend_clean_nocoat_vis_unengaged

---

scene: library_clean_asked

She doesn't even have to think about it. She tells you your answer was right, and she does it without making you feel dumb for asking.

It's a good feeling, knowing you remembered it right, even before you have the packet back in your hands.

Choices:
- Head for Mr. Bradley's room -> junction_clean_vis_unengaged

---

scene: library_clean

Miss Feeney loves books and it shows. There are books on the shelves, book covers tacked all over the walls and even the ceiling, and a book standing up on every table. She's reshelving a cart near the door, and she notices you right away and raises one eyebrow, the friendly way that means shouldn't you be somewhere else?

Choices:
- Ask her about the part of the assignment you're not sure about -> library_clean_asked
- Just keep going -> junction_clean_unc_unengaged

---

scene: hallway_clean

Sunshine pours through the skylights along the broad, bright, clean hallway. It smells like floor wax and Tuesday's lunch. Your backpack is over one shoulder and your sneakers are still bright white.

To your left is the side door out to the playground. Straight ahead and to the right is the way to Mr. Bradley's room and the office. And just past where the hall crosses is the school library.

Choices:
- Head toward Mr. Bradley's room -> junction_clean_unc_unengaged
- Try the side door -> sidedoor_clean
- Stop at the library on the way -> library_clean

---

scene: ending_brief_kickball_scuffed

Two turns before the whistle. The mud somehow stays off. The smudge stays on. You're grinning anyway.

Saturday is going to be a talk. At least you were out there.

THE END

---

scene: ending_brief_sunshine_scuffed

Four minutes of sunshine. Smudged sneaker. The whistle blows.

Still counts.

THE END

---

scene: door_rushing_scuffed

The playground door. Sunshine. Kickball. Mud. The whistle could blow any minute, and the smudge is still on your sneaker. Pick fast.

Choices:
- Go for the kickball game -> ending_brief_kickball_scuffed
- Stay on the blacktop -> ending_brief_sunshine_scuffed

---

scene: mcclintock_rushing_scuffed

She takes the packet. Her eyes move down it fast. She nods.

"Go ahead, Jamie. Hurry up."

You're already moving.

Choices:
- Get to the door -> door_rushing_scuffed

---

scene: folder_scuffed_coat_unc_b_direct

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> mcclintock_rushing_scuffed
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_toolate

---

scene: room10_inside_scuffed_coat_unc_b

You're in the stamp room. Posters of stamps, framed envelopes, fat binders, a big map of the world with a stamp by every country. Any other day you could look around in here forever.

Your brother's desk is easy to find, with his name tag taped on top. Out the window the playground is full and loud and you are not in it. You can tell this is taking longer than it should.

Choices:
- Grab the yellow folder and go -> folder_scuffed_coat_unc_b_direct
- Look around at the stamps for a minute. They'll be quick -> room10_browse_toolate

---

scene: ending_muddy_scuffed

The mud joined the smudge. The kick was worth it. You knew that when you decided, and you'd decide the same way again.

Saturday was already going to be a talk. Now it's a better story.

THE END

---

scene: kickball_ontime_scuffed

Your friends wave you in. The mud joins the smudge. At this point Saturday's talk is going to happen no matter what, so you might as well make it count. You play. You're laughing. The sun is warm.

Choices:
- Slide into first base anyway -> ending_muddy_scuffed

---

scene: ending_careful_scuffed

The sneakers have a smudge. Not a disaster. The sun is still warm, you made it outside, and that counts.

Saturday will be fine. Probably.

THE END

---

scene: blacktop_ontime_scuffed

Your friends wave you toward the field. You point at your sneaker and shake your head. The smudge is there but it didn't get any worse, and that's a small thing but a real one. You find a spot in the sun.

Choices:
- Soak up the sun -> ending_careful_scuffed

---

scene: ending_doorway_scuffed

Fifteen minutes of sunshine with a smudged sneaker. Your friends were glad to see you. The sun was warm.

Saturday is going to be an interesting talk. Right now you find it hard to care.

THE END

---

scene: doorway_ontime_scuffed

You stand in the doorway a second. The smudge catches the light. Then somebody from your class spots you through the fence and yells your name, and you push the door open anyway.

Choices:
- Push the door open and step out into the sun -> ending_doorway_scuffed

---

scene: door_ontime_scuffed

The playground door. Sunshine, blacktop, kickball. The field is muddy from last week's rain. There's already that smudge on your sneaker you've been trying not to think about. Nobody has spotted you yet, and you have time.

Choices:
- Run for the kickball game, even if the field ruins the sneakers -> kickball_ontime_scuffed
- Stay on the blacktop and find your friends -> blacktop_ontime_scuffed
- Just stand here a second -> doorway_ontime_scuffed

---

scene: mcclintock_ontime_scuffed

She takes the packet and reads it over for a moment. Then she looks up.

"You may go outside, Jamie."

Eight words. The best eight words of the whole school year.

Choices:
- Get to the door -> door_ontime_scuffed

---

scene: library_latecheck_scuffed_coat_a

Miss Feeney is still at the desk. She checks your answer in about thirty seconds and tells you you had it right all along. Then comes the walk back to Room 10, and then the walk back toward Room 9, and both of them feel a lot longer than they did the first time.

Choices:
- Head back with the packet -> mcclintock_rushing_scuffed

---

scene: folder_scuffed_coat_unc_a_direct

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> mcclintock_ontime_scuffed
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_scuffed_coat_a

---

scene: folder_scuffed_coat_unc_b_browsed

The yellow folder. Inside is your Explorer packet, in your own handwriting, finished. You did do this. You remember thinking it was right. But now, holding the paper, you're not completely sure about one of the answers. You've already burned a few minutes on the stamps, too.

Choices:
- Trust the work you already did -> mcclintock_rushing_scuffed
- Go all the way back to the library to check -> library_latecheck_toolate

---

scene: room10_browse_scuffed_coat_unc_a

You can't help it. Your brother has an index card about a sculptor named Constantin Brancusi pinned next to a stamp from Romania. There's a first-day cover with a whistling frog on it, a seven-cent stamp from Bermuda. You lose three whole minutes and you find every one of them worth it.

Choices:
- Okay, grab the folder -> folder_scuffed_coat_unc_b_browsed

---

scene: room10_inside_scuffed_coat_unc_a

You're in the stamp room. It's the same size as your own classroom, but it doesn't feel anything like it. Mr. Bradley collects stamps and they're everywhere: posters of stamps, framed envelopes from the first day each stamp came out, fat binders full of them. One whole bulletin board is a map of the world with a different stamp pinned by every country.

Your brother's desk is easy to find. His name tag is taped right on top, with a number line and a plastic cup of Spongebob pencils.

Choices:
- Get the yellow folder out of his desk -> folder_scuffed_coat_unc_a_direct
- Look around at the stamps for a minute -> room10_browse_scuffed_coat_unc_a

---

scene: hallend_scuffed_coat_unc_friendly

The end of the hall. There's a scuffed metal panel nobody ever opens, and one door: Mr. Bradley's room, the stamp teacher the kids call Mr. Potato Head. It's locked, and he's not in it. Mrs. Walker had your coat on the back hook before you finished asking, black with yellow and orange patches, still warm. It's over your arm now. The smudge on your sneaker hasn't gone anywhere.

Choices:
- Wait it out until Mr. Bradley comes back with his key -> room10_inside_scuffed_coat_unc_b
- Run and flag Mr. Bradley down out on the playground -> room10_inside_scuffed_coat_unc_b
- Go borrow Mr. Frank's master key -> room10_inside_scuffed_coat_unc_a

---

